  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pallidal stimulation is effective in patients with generalised idiopathic dystonia. The aim
      of this study is to:

        1. evaluate the efficacy and safety of this treatment in patients with idiopathic
           generalised dystonia, 3 years after surgery and

        2. assess the recurrence of the motor symptoms after the switch off.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
